Xander’s Barber’s Pasta — the viral favorite, made at home!

Start by sautéing garlic paste and marinated chicken (seasoned with salt, pepper, and paprika) until fully cooked.
Then add in chopped tomatoes and cook until they soften.
Next, mix in sun-dried tomatoes along with their olive oil — this is what gives that rich Zander’s flavor!
Season again with salt, pepper, and paprika, then stir in tomato paste — total game changer.
Add a bit of reserved pasta water, give it a good mix, then toss in your boiled pasta.
Top it off with fresh coriander and extra sun-dried tomatoes.
It’s creamy, tangy, and absolutely addictive. Had it with my coffee and I’m making it again for sure!

🤍 Links for the sun-dried tomatoes and tomato paste are in my Naheed Highlights!
